EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 192300 UTC
HIGH PRESSURE 1032 CENTRED SCANDINAVIA FRIDAY EVENING
WITH RIDGE EXTENDING SW ACROSS N SEA AND UK. LOW PRESSURE
OVER GERMANY MAINTAINS A CYCLONIC FLOW IN SEERN N SEA.
THE RIDGE IS THEN EXP TO PERSIST ACROSS THE FCST AREA
DURING SATURDAY. ON SUNDAY CURRENT INDICATIONS ARE FOR
THE RIDGE TO CONTINUE OVER MUCH OF THE AREA BUT WITH A
MORE CYCLONIC FLOW DEVELOPING IN WERN ENGLISH CHANNEL AS
AN ATLANTIC LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM NEARS THE SW OF THE UK.
THIS LOW IS LIKELY TO MOV S AND FILL THROUGH MONDAY. NO
GALES ARE CURRENTLY EXP IN THE CULLERCOATS AREA DURING
THIS FCST PERIOD. STRG WINDS LIKELY AT TIMES EERN N SEA
THROUGH FRIDAY AND SATURDAY SPREADING W FOR A TIME
SATURDAY NIGHT AND SUNDAY THEN BECMG CONFINED TO NEERN N
SEA AREAS EARLY MONDAY. STRG WINDS ALSO LIKELY WERN
ENGLISH CHANNEL THROUGH SUNDAY
